  "faq": {
    "header": "# --- Frequently Asked Questions ---",
    "title": "FAQ",
    "general": "General",
    "participation": "Participation",
    "venueLogistics": "Venue and Logistics",
    "projectDevelopment": "Project Development",
    "q1": "What is HackNU?",
    "a1": "HackNU is a 24-hour hackathon organized by the ACM Student Chapter at Nazarbayev University. It is one of the largest student hackathons in Central Asia.",
    "q2": "When and where will HackNU/26 take place?",
    "a2": "HackNU/26 will take place on April 4-5, 2026 at Nazarbayev University in Astana, Kazakhstan.",
    "q3": "Is participation in HackNU free?",
    "a3": "Yes, participation in HackNU is completely free for all participants.",
    "q4": "Who can participate?",
    "a4": "Students aged 16+ from universities and colleges (Bachelor’s and Master’s programs) are eligible to participate. Participants of all skill levels are welcome.",
    "q5": "Can I participate alone?",
    "a5": "No. Teams must consist of 2-4 members. Participants must form their teams independently before the registration deadline. All registered participants are required to attend the hackathon in person.",
    "q6": "Do I need programming experience?",
    "a6": "Basic programming knowledge is helpful, but participants of all skill levels are welcome. HackNU is a great opportunity to learn and gain hands-on experience.",
    "q7": "Will food be provided?",
    "a7": "Yes. Participants will be provided with one coffee break and one pizza break during the event.",
    "q8": "Can I sleep at the venue?",
    "a8": "According to new university regulations, participants who are not Nazarbayev University students must leave the campus by 22:00. Previously participants were allowed to stay overnight, but updated campus rules now apply.",
    "q9": "What should I bring?",
    "a9": "Please bring your laptop, charger, any hardware you may need for hacking, an extension cord, and your student ID.",
    "q10": "Will there be specific tracks or themes?",
    "a10": "Yes. The tracks and themes will be announced closer to the event. Follow our social media for updates.",
    "q11": "Can I start working on my project before the event?",
    "a11": "No. All development must take place during the 24 hours of the hackathon. You may think about ideas in advance, but writing code before the event is not allowed.",
    "q12": "What tools and technologies can be used?",
    "a12": "You are free to use any programming language, framework, or tool. There are no restrictions."
  },
